    <article class="prose-editorial cs-body" set:html={`<h3>Educational Case Study Disclosure</h3><p>This case study is hypothetical and for educational purposes only. Scenarios, borrower profiles, loan terms, interest rates, and outcomes are illustrative examples and do not represent current offers or guaranteed terms.</p><p>For specific details including down payment requirements, closing cost estimates, interest rate details, closing cost breakdowns, payment calculations, cash-to-close estimates, or an official Loan Estimate, it is highly recommended you<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a meeting with one of our licensed mortgage advisors</a>.</p><p><b>Learn more:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/24/">Asset-based loan cash-out refinance Reg Z advertising requirements (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB official regulation</li><li><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1026">Asset-based loan cash-out refinance Reg Z full text and compliance</a> – Electronic Code of Federal Regulations</li><li><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/interp-24/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Official asset-based loan cash-out refinance advertising interpretations (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB interpretations</li><li><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1014" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Asset-based loan cash-out refinance MAP Rule (Reg N) mortgage advertising</a> – Mortgage advertising rules</li><li><a href="https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/">NMLS Consumer Access – Verify asset-based loan cash-out refinance lender licensure</a></li></ul><p>Actual loan terms vary by credit profile, property, occupancy, location, market conditions, and lender guidelines. For current options tailored to you,<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a consultation</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> apply online</a>.</p><p>Ready to explore your options?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor.</p>		
					<h2>How This Asset-Based Loan Cash-Out Refinance Funded Strategic Business Growth Without Income Verification</h2>				
		<p>Michael P., a 49-year-old serial entrepreneur based in Fort Lauderdale, had successfully built and sold two technology companies over the past 20 years, creating substantial personal wealth held primarily in diversified investment portfolios. Following his second company exit, Michael had spent two years angel investing in early-stage startups while developing plans for his next major venture—a SaaS platform targeting the healthcare industry with significant market potential.</p><p>Michael owned his waterfront primary residence with substantial equity built through appreciation and consistent mortgage paydown. As he prepared to launch his new company, he needed significant capital for initial product development, team hiring, and market entry—but he wanted to avoid diluting his ownership stake through early-stage venture capital or giving up strategic control to outside investors. His substantial home equity represented an ideal capital source that would allow him to maintain full ownership while funding his company's critical initial growth phase.</p><p>However, Michael's income situation presented challenges for traditional cash-out refinancing. Following his company sale, his tax returns showed significant income from the transaction—but that was a one-time event, not ongoing employment. His current income consisted of investment portfolio distributions, angel investment returns, and occasional consulting fees—complex streams that traditional lenders struggled to evaluate using standard underwriting criteria. Additionally, his wealth advisor strongly preferred he keep his substantial investment portfolio intact rather than liquidating positions to fund the business, both to avoid triggering considerable capital gains taxes and to maintain strategic portfolio diversification.</p><p>Michael needed<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/asset-based-loan/"> financing</a> that recognized his substantial financial resources without requiring traditional income verification or employment documentation.</p><p><b>Facing similar challenges?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to explore your options.</p><h2><b>The Challenge: Why Traditional Lenders Couldn't Process This Cash-Out Refinance</b></h2><p>Michael approached three conventional refinance lenders confident that his strong financial position and substantial home equity would make cash-out refinance approval straightforward. He had excellent credit, perfect mortgage payment history, significant net worth demonstrated through liquid assets, and substantial equity in his property. He wanted to access a significant portion of that equity to fund his new company launch.</p><p>All three lenders immediately requested extensive income documentation.</p><h3><b>What Income Documentation Did Traditional Lenders Require?</b></h3><p>Traditional refinance lenders demanded two years of complete tax returns with all schedules, detailed explanations of the company sale transaction and how proceeds were structured, projections of future income from consulting and investments, business plans showing expected income from the new venture, and employer verification letters for any consulting work. The complexity of Michael's post-exit financial structure created extensive underwriting questions that conventional lenders struggled to resolve using standard qualification frameworks.</p><p>"The income documentation requirements were overwhelming," Michael explained. "Yes, I had substantial income from my company sale—but that was in the past, a one-time transaction. My current income streams are diverse: investment portfolio distributions, angel investment returns, occasional consulting fees. Traditional lenders wanted me to prove I had steady ongoing employment-style income sufficient to support the larger mortgage payment after cash-out. But I don't have traditional employment income—I'm an entrepreneur between ventures by choice, not necessity."</p><h3><b>Why Couldn't Traditional Lenders Understand Michael's Financial Capacity?</b></h3><p>The disconnect was profoundly frustrating because Michael's financial capacity was clearly strong by any objective measure. His liquid investment portfolio value exceeded his total mortgage balance significantly—he could pay off the entire mortgage in cash immediately if he chose. He had substantial cash reserves. His credit score was excellent. His home had appreciated substantially. But traditional lenders focused exclusively on monthly income rather than total financial resources.</p><p>"Lenders kept asking 'what's your current monthly income?' as if that was the only measure of financial capacity," Michael said. "I have substantial wealth in liquid investments—diversified portfolios managed by professional advisors. I'm not worried about making mortgage payments—I could pay off the entire mortgage in cash if needed. But they couldn't see past their standard employment income verification requirements to understand my actual financial position."</p><h3><b>What Was at Stake Beyond Just Business Funding?</b></h3><p>The timing pressure added significant urgency. Michael had identified a critical market window for his SaaS platform launch based on industry analysis and competitive intelligence. Competitors were emerging in the healthcare technology space. The regulatory landscape was evolving in ways that favored early movers. Delaying his company launch by months while navigating traditional refinance underwriting could cost him significant first-mover advantage and potentially jeopardize the entire venture's viability.</p><p>Additionally, Michael strongly preferred not to liquidate substantial investment positions to fund the business. His portfolio was well-positioned, performing strongly, and strategically allocated across asset classes according to his wealth advisor's recommendations. Selling positions would trigger substantial capital gains taxes—essentially paying significant fees to the government just to access his own wealth. It would also disrupt his carefully crafted portfolio diversification strategy. He wanted to leverage his home equity—essentially borrowing against one appreciating asset to fund another investment—without disrupting his portfolio or triggering unnecessary tax consequences.</p><h3><b>How Did This Challenge Threaten Michael's Strategic Vision?</b></h3><p>"The smart financial move was accessing home equity through refinancing, not liquidating performing investments and paying capital gains taxes," Michael explained. "But traditional lenders made that impossible with their income verification requirements focused on employment income I didn't have. I needed a solution that recognized my portfolio strength and total financial capacity without requiring me to prove traditional employment income or disrupt my wealth management strategy."</p><p><b>Experiencing similar frustration accessing your equity?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to discuss alternative solutions.</p><h2><b>The Discovery: How Michael Found Asset-Based Cash-Out Refinancing</b></h2><p>While discussing his business funding strategy with his wealth advisor, Michael mentioned his refinance challenges and the documentation barriers he was facing with conventional lenders. The advisor immediately suggested exploring<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/asset-based-loan/"> asset-based cash-out refinance</a> programs designed specifically for high-net-worth entrepreneurs and investors with substantial liquid assets but complex income structures that don't fit traditional underwriting boxes.</p><h3><b>What Made Michael Skeptical About Alternative Financing?</b></h3><p>Intrigued but initially skeptical, Michael scheduled a consultation with a loan advisor specializing in asset-based lending for entrepreneurs and business owners. He doubted that any lender would approve a substantial cash-out refinance without traditional income verification—every lender he'd worked with seemed rigidly focused on employment documentation. But he valued his wealth advisor's recommendation enough to explore the option.</p><h3><b>How Do Asset-Based Lenders Evaluate Borrowers Differently?</b></h3><p>During the consultation, the advisor explained how asset-based cash-out refinancing works fundamentally differently than traditional mortgages. Instead of analyzing income streams and employment verification, asset-based lenders evaluate liquid asset portfolios—stock holdings, bonds, mutual funds, retirement accounts, and other investments. The loan qualification is based on total portfolio value demonstrating financial capacity rather than monthly income documentation or employment status.</p><p>"That conversation completely changed my funding strategy," Michael said. "The advisor explained that with my substantial investment portfolio, I could qualify for cash-out refinancing without providing employment verification, business income projections, or complex income documentation that traditional lenders demanded. The focus would be on my liquid assets—which were more than sufficient to support the refinanced mortgage even with significant cash-out. It was exactly what I needed."</p><h3><b>What Was Michael's "Aha Moment" About Asset-Based Lending?</b></h3><p>The advisor also explained that asset-based lending works particularly well for entrepreneurs between ventures, business owners with complex income structures, and high-net-worth individuals whose wealth is held primarily in investments rather than W-2 employment. These borrowers have real, demonstrable financial capacity—it just doesn't fit traditional lending boxes designed around employment income.</p><p>Michael learned that the approval process would be dramatically streamlined compared to traditional cash-out refinancing. No employment verification needed. No business income projections required. No complex tax return analysis of one-time transactions versus ongoing income. Just portfolio verification and equity confirmation—simple, fast, and focused on his actual financial strength.</p><p>"The asset-based approach aligned perfectly with my situation," Michael added. "I'm not unemployed because I lack financial resources—I'm between ventures because I've been successful enough to choose my next move strategically and fund it myself. Asset-based lenders understand that distinction fundamentally. They focus on total financial capacity, not monthly paystubs or employment letters."</p><h2><b>The Solution: Asset-Based Loan Cash-Out Refinance Approval Process</b></h2><p>Michael worked closely with his loan advisor to assemble the required documentation for an asset-based loan cash-out refinance application. The process focused entirely on his liquid asset portfolio and home equity rather than income verification, dramatically simplifying requirements and accelerating the timeline substantially.</p><h3><b>What Documentation Did Michael Provide for Asset-Based Qualification?</b></h3><p><b>Documentation provided:</b></p><ul><li>Comprehensive investment account statements showing substantial portfolio value across multiple accounts</li><li>Detailed asset portfolio breakdown including stocks, bonds, mutual funds, ETFs, and alternative investments</li><li>Account statements from wealth management firm and multiple brokerage accounts demonstrating diversification</li><li>Excellent credit score with perfect mortgage payment history over years</li><li>Current mortgage balance and recent home value documentation showing substantial equity position</li><li>Strong cash reserves beyond business funding needs</li><li>Brief business plan for new SaaS venture (informational only, not for income qualification purposes)</li><li>No employment verification or traditional income documentation required</li></ul><h3><b>How Long Did the Asset-Based Cash-Out Refinance Process Take?</b></h3><p><b>The approval timeline:</b></p><ol><li><b>Initial consultation (Day 1)</b> — Discussed business funding strategy, asset-based qualification approach, and refinancing goals</li><li><b>Asset portfolio review (Days 1-3)</b> — Analyzed total liquid asset values, portfolio composition, and asset quality</li><li><b>Pre-qualification confirmed (Day 4)</b> — Verified eligibility for substantial cash-out based on portfolio strength</li><li><b>Document submission (Days 5-7)</b> — Uploaded investment account statements and property documentation through secure portal</li><li><b>Asset verification (Days 8-12)</b> — Asset-based lender verified portfolio values directly with custodians and investment managers</li><li><b>Credit review (Days 13-14)</b> — Verified excellent credit score and perfect mortgage payment history</li><li><b>Property appraisal ordered (Day 15)</b> — Scheduled appraisal to confirm current home value and available equity</li><li><b>Appraisal completed (Day 21)</b> — Waterfront property appraised at favorable value confirming substantial equity</li><li><b>Underwriting approval (Day 23)</b> — Approved for substantial cash-out refinance based on asset portfolio strength</li><li><b>Final document review (Days 24-26)</b> — Completed remaining documentation and final conditions</li><li><b>Clear to close (Day 27)</b> — Final approval granted with all conditions satisfied</li><li><b>Closing scheduled (Day 30)</b> — Closed on cash-out refinance exactly 30 days after initial application</li></ol><h3><b>How Did Asset-Based Lenders Calculate Michael's Qualification?</b></h3><p>The asset-based lender evaluated Michael's substantial liquid investment portfolio and applied qualification criteria based on total portfolio value and asset quality. Rather than calculating debt-to-income ratios based on employment income, they assessed his total financial resources and determined that his portfolio provided more than sufficient financial capacity to support the refinanced mortgage with significant cash-out.</p><p>This approach recognized the reality that high-net-worth individuals often have wealth structured in investments rather than employment income. Michael's portfolio demonstrated far stronger financial capacity than any monthly paycheck could show—he literally could pay off the entire mortgage immediately if needed, though that wasn't the optimal wealth management strategy.</p><h3><b>What Made Michael's Application Particularly Strong?</b></h3><p>Several factors strengthened Michael's asset-based application beyond just his portfolio value. His excellent credit score demonstrated financial responsibility and reliability. His perfect mortgage payment history showed he understood obligations and honored commitments. His diversified portfolio across multiple asset classes showed sophisticated wealth management rather than speculative positions. His substantial home equity reduced lender risk. And his clear, well-developed business plan demonstrated strategic thinking even though income projections weren't used for qualification.</p><p>The combination of substantial liquid assets, excellent credit, perfect payment history, strong equity position, and strategic business planning positioned Michael as a low-risk borrower using asset-based qualification criteria—arguably lower risk than many employed borrowers with high debt-to-income ratios and minimal reserves.</p><p><b>Ready to access your equity for business purposes?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> Get approved</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a call</a> to discuss your entrepreneurial financing strategy.</p><h2><b>The Results: How Did Asset-Based Financing Enable Michael's Business Launch?</b></h2><p>Michael closed on his cash-out refinance in exactly 30 days after submitting his initial application—meeting his timeline goals and enabling him to launch his SaaS platform on schedule. He extracted substantial equity from his waterfront property and immediately deployed that capital toward product development, initial team hiring, and market entry activities critical to establishing competitive positioning.</p><h3><b>What Were the Final Terms of Michael's Cash-Out Refinance?</b></h3><p><b>Final loan outcome:</b></p><ul><li>Approved substantial cash-out refinance based entirely on investment portfolio qualification</li><li>Competitive interest rate given his excellent credit and strong financial position</li><li>Favorable long-term fixed-rate structure providing payment predictability</li><li>Manageable monthly payment that his investment income easily supported</li><li>Timeline: Application to closing in exactly 30 days</li><li>Substantial equity extracted for business capitalization</li><li>Portfolio remained fully invested and working—no liquidation required</li><li>No capital gains taxes triggered from asset sales</li></ul><h3><b>How Did Asset-Based Qualification Compare to Traditional Lending?</b></h3><p><b>Traditional lender approach vs. asset-based lender approach:</b></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><b>Qualification Factor</b></p></td><td><p><b>Traditional Lender</b></p></td><td><p><b>Asset-Based Lender</b></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Primary qualification basis</b></p></td><td><p>Employment income verification</p></td><td><p>Liquid investment portfolio value</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Documentation required</b></p></td><td><p>Extensive income documentation</p></td><td><p>Simplified asset verification</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Tax return analysis</b></p></td><td><p>Complex multi-year analysis required</p></td><td><p>Not required</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Business income projections</b></p></td><td><p>Required and scrutinized</p></td><td><p>Not required for qualification</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Employment verification</b></p></td><td><p>Required</p></td><td><p>Not required</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Portfolio consideration</b></p></td><td><p>Ignored or secondary</p></td><td><p>Primary qualification factor</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Approval timeline</b></p></td><td><p>Extended (weeks to months)</p></td><td><p>Streamlined (under 30 days)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Business funding goal</b></p></td><td><p>BLOCKED ❌</p></td><td><p>ACHIEVED ✅</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Portfolio preservation</b></p></td><td><p>Not considered</p></td><td><p>Explicitly supported ✅</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Capital gains avoidance</b></p></td><td><p>Not addressed</p></td><td><p>Strategic benefit ✅</p></td></tr></tbody></table><h3><b>What Immediate Results Did Michael Achieve?</b></h3><p>"Without asset-based lending, I would have faced an impossible choice: abandon my business launch timing, dilute ownership through venture capital, or liquidate investments and pay substantial capital gains taxes," Michael explained. "None of those options aligned with smart wealth management or strategic business planning. Asset-based financing gave me a fourth option—leverage existing equity efficiently while keeping my investment portfolio intact and working."</p><p>Michael launched his healthcare SaaS platform on schedule with full funding in place. He hired key team members without delay. He began product development immediately. He entered the market during the optimal window he'd identified, ahead of emerging competitors. And he maintained full ownership and strategic control—no venture capital dilution, no outside board seats, no constraints on his decision-making or exit timing.</p><h3><b>How Does This Fit Into Michael's Bigger Wealth-Building Strategy?</b></h3><p>Michael views the cash-out refinance as smart capital deployment within a broader wealth management framework. The home equity was essentially idle capital—building slowly through appreciation but not generating returns. By accessing that equity to fund a high-potential business venture, he's putting capital to work at potentially much higher returns while maintaining his diversified investment portfolio.</p><p>"Sophisticated wealth management is about strategic leverage," Michael said. "I'm borrowing at favorable mortgage rates to fund a business with significantly higher return potential. My investment portfolio continues growing uninterrupted. My home continues appreciating. And I'm building potential significant value through the business—all without triggering taxes, disrupting portfolio positions, or diluting ownership. That's how you compound wealth intelligently."</p><h3><b>What Are Michael's Long-Term Plans?</b></h3><p>When the SaaS company reaches profitability, Michael plans to retain ownership and grow the business organically using cash flow rather than external funding. If he eventually exits through acquisition or sale, the proceeds will significantly exceed the equity he accessed through refinancing, creating substantial wealth multiplication. Meanwhile, his investment portfolio and home equity continue growing independently.</p><p>For future ventures or real estate opportunities, Michael now has an established relationship with asset-based lenders who understand his financial structure. He knows he can access capital efficiently without disrupting his wealth management strategy or triggering unnecessary taxes.</p><p><b>Ready to get started on your business funding strategy?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> Get approved</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a call</a> to discuss your situation.</p><h2><b>Exploring Other Asset-Based Loan Options?</b></h2><p>While Michael used an asset-based loan for cash-out refinancing to fund business growth, asset-based financing works for multiple scenarios:</p><ul><li><b>Need to purchase property?</b> See how an<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-purchase"> investment banker used asset-based loan purchase for luxury waterfront home</a> with quick approval</li><li><b>Want to refinance and lower your rate?</b> See how a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-refinance/"> retired executive used asset-based loan refinance to reduce monthly payments</a> without income verification</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> to find success stories matching your financial situation</li></ul><h2><b>Key Takeaways for Entrepreneurs and Business Owners</b></h2><h3><b>What Can Entrepreneurs Learn from This Asset-Based Loan Cash-Out Refinance Success?</b></h3><ul><li><b>Asset-based cash-out refinancing qualifies borrowers based on liquid portfolio values, not traditional income</b>—perfect for entrepreneurs between ventures or with complex compensation structures that don't fit standard employment income boxes. This approach recognizes that wealth comes in many forms, and substantial liquid assets demonstrate financial capacity more reliably than monthly paystubs for high-net-worth individuals (<a href="https://www.sba.gov/funding-programs">SBA business financing resources</a>)<p> </p></li><li><b>Accessing home equity can be more strategic than venture capital for early-stage funding</b>—maintain full ownership, avoid dilution, preserve complete control over strategic decisions and exit timing. Michael's approach allowed him to fund critical business growth without giving up equity or board seats to outside investors<p> </p></li><li><b>Preserving investment portfolios avoids capital gains taxes and maintains diversification</b>—borrowing against one asset to fund another investment is often significantly smarter than liquidating performing holdings and triggering substantial tax consequences. Michael kept his portfolio working while accessing needed capital (<a href="https://www.irs.gov/taxtopics/tc409">IRS capital gains guidance</a>)<p> </p></li><li><b>Streamlined approval timelines enable entrepreneurs to act quickly on market opportunities</b>—asset-based loans close faster than traditional financing, often in under 30 days, which can be critical when timing matters for competitive positioning or market windows<p> </p></li><li><b>High-net-worth borrowers benefit from dramatically simplified documentation</b>—no employment verification, no business income projections, no complex tax return analysis required. Focus purely on what matters: demonstrable financial capacity through liquid assets<p> </p></li><li><b>Excellent credit profiles unlock competitive rates even with alternative qualification</b>—strong credit helped Michael secure favorable pricing despite non-traditional income structure and complex financial situation. Credit quality remains important regardless of qualification method<p> </p></li></ul><p><b>Have questions about using home equity to fund business ventures?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor experienced in entrepreneur financing.</p><h2><b>Alternative Loan Programs for Entrepreneurs and Business Owners</b></h2><p>If an asset-based loan cash-out refinance isn't the perfect fit for your situation, consider these alternative financing options:</p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/bank-statement-loan/">Bank Statement Loan</a> – Cash-out refinance using business bank deposits for self-employed entrepreneurs with strong cash flow</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/dscr-loan/">DSCR Loan</a> – Investment property financing based on rental income, no personal income verification required</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/portfolio-loan/">Portfolio Loan</a> – Finance multiple properties with flexible terms for real estate investors building portfolios</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/heloc/">HELOC</a> – Access equity through flexible line of credit without refinancing first mortgage</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/home-equity-loan/">Home Equity Loan</a> – Fixed-rate second lien to access equity while preserving first mortgage terms</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/p-and-l-loan/">P&amp;L Loan (Profit and Loss)</a> – Qualify using CPA-prepared financial statements showing consistent business profitability</li></ul><p><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/">Explore all loan programs</a> to find your best option.</p><p>Want to assess your complete financial picture?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/discovery-quiz/"> Take our discovery quiz</a> to clarify your wealth-building and business goals.</p><h2><b>Helpful Asset-Based Loan Cash-Out Refinance Resources</b></h2><p><b>Learn more about this loan program:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/asset-based-loan/">Complete Asset-Based Loan Guide</a> – Detailed requirements and qualification guidelines for portfolio-based lending</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculator/asset-based-loan-calculator">Asset-Based Loan Calculator</a> – Estimate how much equity you can access based on your portfolio value</li></ul><p><b>Similar success stories:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-purchase">How an investment banker purchased luxury home with asset-based loan</a> – Quick-close purchase success in competitive market</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-refinance/">Retired executive's asset-based refinance success</a> – Improving terms with portfolio assets</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> – Browse by financial situation and goals</li></ul><p><b>External authoritative resources:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.sba.gov/funding-programs">SBA Business Financing Resources</a> – Small Business Administration funding guidance and programs</li><li><a href="https://www.irs.gov/taxtopics/tc409">IRS Capital Gains Guidance</a> – Tax considerations for investment decisions and asset liquidation</li><li><a href="https://www.investor.gov/">SEC Investor Resources</a> – Investment portfolio management and securities regulations</li></ul><p><b>Ready to get started?</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/">Apply online</a> – Start your cash-out refinance application today</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/">Schedule a consultation</a> – Discuss your business funding strategy with experienced advisors</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/discovery-quiz/">Take the discovery quiz</a> – Deep dive into your wealth-building and entrepreneurial goals</li></ul><p>Need local expertise?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/get-a-local-introduction/"> Get introduced to trusted partners</a> including business advisors and wealth management specialists.</p><p><b>Disclosure:</b> <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/nexa-mortgage-partnership/"  data-wpil-monitor-id="313">NEXA Mortgage</a>, LLC dba Stairway Mortgage — NMLS #1660690 • Equal Housing Lender. Applications are handled by state-licensed Mortgage Loan Originators; you will be matched with an MLO licensed in your state. Not all products are available in all states. See our<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/licenses-disclosures"> Licenses &amp; Disclosures</a> page for state-specific information. This case study is for educational and illustrative purposes only. Scenarios, borrowers, and loan terms may be hypothetical and are used to demonstrate potential financing solutions. Not a commitment to lend. All loans are subject to credit approval, program availability, and underwriting guidelines. Interest rates, fees, loan amounts, and other terms are examples and do not represent current offers or market rates. Actual terms vary by applicant profile, property, market conditions, and lender guidelines, and may change without notice. Asset-based lending involves pledging liquid assets as collateral or qualification basis; specific lender requirements vary regarding asset types, liquidity, and portfolio composition. Texas homestead cash-out refinance is limited to 80% LTV and subject to Texas Constitution, Article XVI, §50(a)(6), including a 12-day waiting period before closing. Using home equity to fund business ventures involves risk; businesses may fail, and borrowers remain obligated to repay mortgages regardless of business outcomes. For current terms specific to your situation, please<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a consultation</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> apply online</a>. NMLS Consumer Access:<a href="https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/"> https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/</a></p>		
